findings.description:
The modified `testRW11ACXX01` method in step 2)-1a is shown only as bare assertion lines, omitting the complete `execute()` call with the `BasicAdvice` anonymous class wrapper. The knowledge file shows:
```java
W11ACXXForm actual = context.getRequestScopedVar("W11ACXX");
assertObjectPropertyEquals(message, sheetName, "expectedUsers", actual.getUsers());
```
but the source provides the full structure:
```java
execute("testRW11ACXX01", new BasicAdvice() {
    @Override
    public void afterExecute(TestCaseInfo testCaseInfo, ExecutionContext context) {
        String message = testCaseInfo.getTestCaseName();
        String sheetName = testCaseInfo.getSheetName();
        W11ACXXForm actual = context.getRequestScopedVar("W11ACXX");
        assertObjectPropertyEquals(message, sheetName, "expectedUsers", actual.getUsers());
    }
});
```
The `BasicAdvice`, `TestCaseInfo`, `afterExecute`, `getTestCaseName()`, and `getSheetName()` are entirely absent. An AI providing implementation guidance from this knowledge file would generate incomplete/incorrect code.

